{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout is organized as a single-column list to maximize screen real estate and provide a clear, scannable hierarchy.  Items are vertically stacked with consistent spacing to maintain a clean and organized feel. Section dividers are used to visually group related settings, improving readability and user comprehension. Padding is strategically used to create visual breathing room without double-padding issues.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is linear, following a top-to-bottom navigation.  Each setting is presented as a tappable list item, leading to a subsequent screen for editing (for editable settings) or performing the immediate action (for toggle switches).  The 'What is it?' links provide additional context, enhancing understanding. This approach reduces cognitive load and enables quick access to required settings.",
    "componentChoices": "The design leverages the provided design system, ensuring a cohesive and consistent user experience. List items (ItemText) are employed to display settings options and their current state (e.g. 'Active' switch). Toggles (ItemSwitch) facilitate immediate action without navigation for boolean preferences.  Navigation icons (ic_24_forward) are used to clearly indicate where further interaction is needed. Info components (ItemText) provide additional context.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through clear labeling, consistent spacing, and the use of section dividers. Important settings (e.g., account deletion) are placed lower in the list, while less critical settings appear higher, guiding user focus according to task priority. The use of color (Neutral/neutral90, Neutral/neutral80) and typography (Title/title_s) supports visual distinction.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "Variants are selected to match specific user requirements and context.  'Editable' items use 'Trailing: Icon' variants to indicate navigation. Toggles utilize 'Trailing: Switch' variants.  The 'Delete my account permanently' option employs the 'Color: Error' variant to highlight its destructive nature. 'What is it?' links use the 'Trailing: Info' variant to present help content.  The 'Access to Cars45 auction' option is styled with the 'State: Active' to show the current state."
  }
}
